WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.180
Welcome to the Stash Budget App. Let's
explore how it helps you manage money

00:00:04.180 --> 00:00:08.860
smarter. Not just follow steps, but
understand why each feature matters.

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:13.960
Start by creating an account, like a
checking or savings account.

00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:17.760
Add your current balance. This is your
financial snapshot.

00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:22.360
It helps you track everything in one
place, so you know exactly what's

00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:27.300
available to spend. Now, log expenses as
you

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:31.600
spend. Categorize them, like groceries or
bills, to see patterns.

00:00:32.439 --> 00:00:35.840
This isn't just recording. It shows you
where money goes,

00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:39.420
helping you cut back on impulse buys and
build better habits.

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:44.060
Transfers move money between accounts
without real-world fees.

00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:49.520
It's like reallocating funds digitally.
Great for saving or paying

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:54.480
bills. This keeps your finances organized
and prevents overdrafts.

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:59.080
The Transactions tab is your history log.
It lists

00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:03.020
everything chronologically so you can
review spending and spot trends,

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:07.940
like Am I spending too much on dining?
This builds awareness for

00:01:07.940 --> 00:01:12.800
smarter decisions. Statistics visualize
your

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:16.940
data with charts. See spending by category
or overtime.

00:01:16.940 --> 00:01:20.900
It reveals habits you might miss, like
monthly spikes,

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:25.900
helping you plan ahead and save more.
Budget set limits

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:30.800
per category to avoid overspending. Set
one, like for groceries,

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:35.220
and track progress. If you add an expense
that exceeds it,

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:38.900
the app alerts you, teaching discipline
and preventing debt.

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:43.000
The tutorial tab walks you through basics
if you're new.

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:47.120
It's like a built-in guide. Quick tips on
accounts, expenses,

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:51.980
and more. Use it anytime to refresh your
knowledge. Settings

00:01:51.980 --> 00:01:56.720
customize the app to you. Adjust font size
for

00:01:56.720 --> 00:02:01.540
readability. Switch to dark

00:02:01.540 --> 00:02:04.820
mode for night use, and clear your data.

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:09.160
It ensures the app fits your style and
needs.